        "146": {
          "vnum": 146,
          "name": "Clicker Cavern",
          "description": "The clickers have been awfully busy, for this burrowed cavern is huge to say the least. And what happened to all the rock that was once here? Gazing carefully at one of the nearby insectoid beasts, the thought crosses your mind that the little critters might actually eat the stuff. The sprawling cavern continues to the north and west, and a runed tunnel leads through the rock to the east.",
